{"questionId":"9076531","questionHtml":"<p>Two radioactive nuclides, X and Y, have half-lives of 50 s and 100 s respectively. At time <em>t </em>= 0 samples of X and Y contain the same number of nuclei.</p>\n<p>What is&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{number of nuclei of X undecayed}}}}{{{\\text{number of nuclei of Y undecayed}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>number of nuclei of X undecayed</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>number of nuclei of Y undecayed</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;when <em>t </em>= 200 s?</p>\n<p>A. &nbsp; &nbsp; 4</p>\n<p>B. &nbsp; &nbsp; 2</p>\n<p>C. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>D. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{4}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076531","referenceCode":"18M.1.HL.TZ1.37","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Two radioactive nuclides, X and Y, have half-lives of 50 s and 100 s respectively. At time t = 0 samples of X and Y contain the same number of nuclei. What is number of nuclei of X","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"37","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 12: Quantum and nuclear physics","12.1 – The interaction of matter with radiation","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 12: Quantum and nuclear physics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}